{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a66dc06c-8263-4f61-a933-69a5ee3707f5","content":"The directory is empty, so I'll provide the recommended setup from MSTest best practices:\n\n## 1. Simplest project file using MSTest.Sdk\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` brings in the test framework, runner, and analyzers automatically.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution\n\nAdd a `.runsettings` file (or an `AssemblyInfo.cs`). The simplest way:\n\n```csharp\n// In your project, add this attribute (e.g., in a Usings.cs or AssemblyInfo.cs)\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs all test methods in parallel across classes.\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nDecorate your integration test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Query_Records() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n| Concern | Mechanism |\n|---------|-----------|\n| SDK project | `Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\"` (no explicit package refs needed) |\n| Parallel by default | `[assembly: Parallelize]` |\n| Sequential for DB tests | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n\nThe `[DoNotParallelize]` tests will run after all parallel tests complete, ensuring no shared-state conflicts with your database.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"57e83684-810c-4120-91ba-e5c6aeaca6ae","outputTokens":436,"requestId":"E3C8:165513:190EDBF:1C087EF:6A052B32"},"id":"e1c8ef47-fd88-4197-aeee-0e1c14d9c977","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:54:05.394Z","parentId":"98eaf267-b946-4d12-a2d8-5783a53abdb7"}
